CatDescriptText: The signs hanging above the bar read, "Credit is Dead It Was Killed by the Last Man Who did not Pay", "Positively No Ladies Served At Bar', and "Don't Ask for Credit".
TitMainTitle: Interior of bar with tin ceiling, neon sign of two baseball bats and ball in glass block window, and sign reading "Positively no ladies served at bar," possibly Montooth Hotel, on Montooth Street and Lafferty Avenue
